topicSummary: An ectopic pregnancy develops outside the uterine cavity with most occurring in the fallopian tubes.

topicHtmlObjects.htmlHeader: Ectopic pregnancy: Summary

latestChanges.title: Minor update
latestChanges.body: The section on Managing suspected ectopic pregnancy has been clarified, and information on anti-D immunoglobulin for rhesus-negative women who have had surgical removal of an ectopic pregnancy has been included in the section on Follow up after an ectopic pregnancy.

latestChanges.title: Revised
latestChanges.body: A literature search was conducted in February 2018 to identify evidence-based guidelines, UK policy, systematic reviews, and key randomized controlled trials (RCTs) published since the last revision of the topic. No changes to clinical recommendations have been made.
